svg.desc: The chart shows that the proportion of men and women with a BMI over 30 increased between 1999 and 2013 in all five shown age groups between 18 and 64, with the risk of becoming obese increasing with age. The proportion of men and women with a BMI of 30 and above is largest among those aged 55 to 64. Every fourth man and every fifth woman in this age group was obese in 2013. In the case of young adults (18 to 24) this only applies to every 20th person, but this group shows the largest percentage increases at 65 percent. This finding is also relevant in view of the increasing prevalence of obesity among children and adolescents.

div.p:
Source: Statistisches Bundesamt, Microsensus, own calculations.
